			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">To simplify the PNaCl ABI, PNaCl should restrict the integer types allowed in PNaCl executables to i1, i8, i16, i32 and i64.  This will simplify the language that a PNaCl translator needs to handle.

I don't think Clang will generate code using integer types other than those in this list (except perhaps for vector operations, which we don't support yet).

Unusual integer types will only appear where LLVM optimisation passes have introduced them.  We can disable the parts of the optimisation passes that do this.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-05-31T02:33:06.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-04-01T01:18:45.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
